---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lessons = [
  {
    jp: '謙虚',
    rom: 'kenkyo',
    en: 'humility',
    body: 'The most accomplished engineers in the room were the quietest. The CEO bowed deeper than the intern. Humility wasn\'t a performance — it was the baseline. I grew up thinking humility was something you practised. In Japan I realised it was something you were.',
  },
  {
    jp: '時間',
    rom: 'jikan',
    en: 'time',
    body: 'Trains arrived to the second. Meetings started before they started. If a delivery was promised for 10:00 AM, it was ready at 9:55. Time wasn\'t something you managed. It was something you respected — and you kept your part of the contract so others could keep theirs.',
  },
  {
    jp: '勤勉',
    rom: 'kinben',
    en: 'diligence',
    body: 'Not long hours for their own sake — focused, painstaking, careful hours. The last person to leave wasn\'t performing. They were finishing something they\'d said they would finish. The difference between "hard work" and "working hard" is everything, and Japan taught me which one compounds.',
  },
  {
    jp: '改善',
    rom: 'kaizen',
    en: 'continuous improvement',
    body: 'Not big rewrites — ten small fixes nobody notices individually, accumulated over a decade. By the time I understood kaizen wasn\'t a business-book buzzword but a daily practice, I couldn\'t unsee it. It\'s how good systems stay good.',
  },
];

---

<BaseLayout title="Japan — Venkateshwar Reddy Jambula">
  <article class="jp">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="jp-header">
      <a href="/" class="jp-back">&larr; home</a>
      <div class="jp-eyebrow">~a year of trips &middot; my early Bosch days &middot; the chapter that quietly reshaped me</div>
      <h1>Japan.</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Opening pull -->
    <section class="jp-opener">
      <p class="jp-lede">
        I landed at Haneda in my early twenties with a passport that had
        barely been used, and the next roughly twelve months of trips
        back and forth to Yokohama showed a young Indian engineer what
        a civilisation looks like when it takes the unglamorous things
        seriously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Two postcards -->
    <div class="postcards">
      <figure class="postcard postcard-a">
        <img
          src="/images/japan/friends-yokohama.jpg"
          alt="Venkat with Indian friends in a Yokohama apartment"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <figcaption>yokohama &middot; a friend&rsquo;s apartment</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="postcard postcard-b">
        <img
          src="/images/japan/friends-tokyo-street.jpg"
          alt="Venkat with Japanese colleagues on a Tokyo street at night"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <figcaption>tokyo &middot; friends who stayed friends</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <!-- The civilisational frame -->
    <section class="jp-section">
      <h2>A civilisation I didn&rsquo;t know was possible.</h2>
      <p>
        I grew up in India assuming cities were loud because cities are
        loud. That people were late because that was the human default.
        That traffic was traffic. Japan patiently disabused me of those
        assumptions in the first couple of weeks. Tokyo quiet enough that
        you can hear your own footsteps. Trains moving enormous volumes
        of people, arriving to the second. Strangers running half a
        block to return a forgotten glove.
      </p>
      <p>
        It wasn&rsquo;t that Japan had fewer problems. It was that the
        problems it chose to solve &mdash; punctuality, humility,
        cleanliness, reliability, craft &mdash; were the ones most
        civilisations had quietly given up on. For a young engineer
        barely out of college, watching a country do the unglamorous
        things <em>well</em> changed what I thought was possible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- The four words -->
    <section class="jp-section">
      <h2>Four words I took home with me.</h2>
      <p class="note">
        Not buzzwords. Not kanji tattoos. Practices I saw in the people
        around me, and have tried to carry since.
      </p>

      <div class="lesson-grid">
        {lessons.map((l) => (
          <article class="lesson">
            <div class="l-kanji" aria-hidden="true">{l.jp}</div>
            <div class="l-rom">
              <em>{l.rom}</em> &mdash; {l.en}
            </div>
            <p>{l.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Trains + landscapes -->
    <section class="jp-section two-col">
      <div>
        <h3>The trains.</h3>
        <p>
          You don&rsquo;t really understand punctuality until you&rsquo;ve
          watched a train leave a platform at exactly 09:00:00 and
          realised nobody on the platform finds this remarkable. Japan&rsquo;s
          trains weren&rsquo;t engineering to me. They were an ethics.
        </p>
        <p>
          Even a two-minute delay came with a printed apology. I remember
          the first time I saw that note and thought, this is a country
          that takes its word seriously.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>The landscapes.</h3>
        <p>
          Mount Fuji from a train window on a cold morning. The Pacific
          at Kamakura. The stone paths around the old shrines in the
          middle of Tokyo. Quiet corners of cities I&rsquo;d only seen
          in movies.
        </p>
        <p>
          I used to think I needed quiet to think. Japan taught me what
          quiet actually is.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Friendships -->
    <section class="jp-section">
      <h2>The friendships.</h2>
      <p>
        The other young Indian engineers I travelled with became close
        friends in a way that&rsquo;s hard to explain if you haven&rsquo;t
        been twenty-something and thousands of kilometres from home.
        Small Yokohama apartments, late dinners, cheap ramen, shared
        surprise at everything around us. Khichdi on Sunday. Cricket
        arguments at 2 AM. Showing up for each other&rsquo;s hard weeks.
      </p>
      <p>
        A few of those friendships are the kind that survive the years
        and the continents. That wasn&rsquo;t something I expected to
        bring home from a work trip, but it was the most lasting thing
        I did.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Being Indian in Japan -->
    <section class="jp-section">
      <h2>Being a young Indian in Japan.</h2>
      <p>
        A quiet part of that year was being young, Indian, visibly
        foreign, and trying to fit into a workplace culture that had
        its own assumptions about how people from my part of the world
        behaved. I won&rsquo;t speak for anyone else, but for me the
        answer wasn&rsquo;t to argue back. It was to listen more than I
        spoke, show up earlier than I needed to, finish what I said I
        would, and let the work do the talking.
      </p>
      <p>
        I came home with a clearer sense of which Indian habits I
        wanted to keep and which ones Japan had quietly, firmly asked
        me to reconsider.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- The bridge back -->
    <section class="jp-section jp-close">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          I came back to India with a few Japanese words, a permanent
          suspicion of the phrase &ldquo;move fast,&rdquo; and a
          mental image of what careful work looks like when a whole
          country agrees to take it seriously.
        </p>
        <p>
          Years later, when I sit down to build something for other
          humans to depend on, I&rsquo;m still measuring what I do
          against what I saw in Yokohama in my early twenties.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <footer class="jp-foot">
      <a href="/" class="jp-back-cta">&larr; back to the story</a>
    </footer>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .jp {
    max-width: 840px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 40px 120px;
  }

  /* ============ HEADER ============ */
  .jp-header {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 24px 0 40px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .jp-back {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 6px 12px;
    background: var(--paper-card);
    border-radius: 3px;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.12);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .jp-back:hover { color: var(--accent-red); text-decoration: none; }

  .jp-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .jp h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(72px, 11vw, 128px);
    line-height: 0.9;
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  /* ============ OPENER ============ */
  .jp-opener {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto 48px;
  }
  .jp-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.8vw, 28px);
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink-headline);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .jp-lede em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-red);
  }

  /* ============ POSTCARDS (two small photos) ============ */
  .postcards {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 40px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 24px 0 72px;
  }
  .postcard {
    width: 280px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 10px 10px 34px;
    background: var(--paper-card);
    box-shadow:
      0 2px 4px rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.12),
      0 16px 36px rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.18);
    position: relative;
    transition: transform 0.35s var(--ease-reveal), box-shadow 0.35s;
  }
  .postcard-a { transform: rotate(-2.5deg); }
  .postcard-b { transform: rotate(2deg); }
  .postcard:hover {
    transform: rotate(0deg) translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow:
      0 4px 8px rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.15),
      0 22px 48px rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.24);
    z-index: 5;
  }
  /* tape */
  .postcard::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -12px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%) rotate(-3deg);
    width: 90px;
    height: 22px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(240, 230, 180, 0.72), rgba(240, 230, 180, 0.88));
    border-left: 1px dashed rgba(120, 100, 60, 0.18);
    border-right: 1px dashed rgba(120, 100, 60, 0.18);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }
  .postcard-b::before { transform: translateX(-50%) rotate(4deg); }

  .postcard img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 180px;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: saturate(0.95) contrast(1.02);
  }
  .postcard figcaption {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 8px;
    left: 10px;
    right: 10px;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-hand);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  /* ============ SECTIONS ============ */
  .jp-section {
    margin: 72px 0;
  }
  .jp-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 44px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .jp-section h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .jp-section p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }
  .jp-section p em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-headline);
  }
  .jp-section .note {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    max-width: 620px;
  }
  .jp-section.two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
  }

  /* ============ LESSON GRID ============ */
  .lesson-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  .lesson {
    padding: 28px 24px 24px;
    background: var(--paper-card);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.08), 0 10px 24px rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.12);
  }
  .l-kanji {
    font-family: 'Noto Serif JP', 'Hiragino Mincho ProN', 'YuMincho', serif;
    font-size: 60px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--accent-red);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .l-rom {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .l-rom em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-red);
  }
  .lesson p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ============ STEREOTYPE GRID ============ */
  .stereo-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px dashed rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.15);
  }
  .stereo {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 28px 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 16px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.15);
  }
  .s-they {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .s-sep {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--accent-red);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .s-me {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--ink-headline);
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .stereo-close {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 19px !important;
    line-height: 1.5 !important;
    color: var(--ink-headline) !important;
    margin-top: 32px !important;
    padding-left: 16px;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-red);
  }

  /* ============ CLOSE ============ */
  .jp-close blockquote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 24px 0 24px 28px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-red);
  }
  .jp-close blockquote p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.6vw, 24px);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-headline);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .jp-close blockquote p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* ============ FOOTER ============ */
  .jp-foot {
    margin-top: 80px;
    padding-top: 32px;
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px dashed rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.15);
  }
  .jp-back-cta {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--accent-red);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(194, 54, 23, 0.3);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .jp-back-cta:hover { text-decoration: none; border-bottom-color: var(--accent-red); }

  /* ============ MOBILE ============ */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .jp { padding: 32px 20px 80px; }
    .jp-back { position: relative; display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .jp-section.two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 24px; }
    .lesson-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .stereo { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 6px; text-align: left; }
    .s-sep { text-align: left; }
  }
</style>
